{meta: title She Will Get Lonesome}
{meta: artist The Louvin Brothers}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]I told my heart last night you were gone
And it started pleading with [G7]me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Go tell the stars and they will twinkle
And make her lonesome and [C]dream
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
Please Mister Moon let [F]the [C]stars
[G7]Come out and play until the breaking of [C]day
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
And they will twinkle and my baby will see them
And she will get lonesome and [G7]come back home to [C]me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
The moon said yes I'll let them play
And twinkle with all their [G7]might
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
If you'll get the clouds to hide my face
From this lonesome [C]night
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
Please Mister Wind blow [F]the [C]clouds
[G7]They'll hide the moon from the lonesome [C]night
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 8}
Then the stars will twinkle and my baby will see them
And she will get lonesome and [G7]come back home to [C]me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 9}
Then the wind blew the clouds and hid the moon
The stars all twinkled so [G7]bright
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 10}
But there in a flash my whole world crashed
When I got heaven's [C]reply
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 11}
They told my you'd [F]found someone [C]new
[G7]And there was nothing they could [C]do
Then I told the stars and they quit [G7]twinkling
They told the moon and it began to [C]cry
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 12}
The moon told the wind and it began to moan
The wind told the clouds and by and [F]by
[G7]The rain came falling [C]down
{end_of_verse}
